en_661798_0	President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa has said that measures should be taken to accelerate the development of the education sector as a priority.
en_661798_1	The President made this statement participating at a meeting held at the Presidential Secretariat.
en_661798_2	President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa had a special discussion at the Presidential Secretariat with Education and Higher Education Ministers as well as institutional officials.
en_661798_3	The President drew his attention to rapid changes in many aspects of the education sector.
en_661798_4	President Rajapaksa stressed the need for an education system that would enable the younger generation of the world to have access to a technology-driven global economy.
en_661798_5	The President emphasized at this meeting that the examination centered education system should be set up so that the burden of the burden placed on the children is eliminated.
en_661798_6	It was also explained the importance of focusing on the needs of the country as well as the international level syllabus and curriculum.
en_661798_7	President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa also stressed the importance of politicians to make decisions regarding education beyond politics.
en_661798_8	The President said that speedy measures should be taken to train the unemployed graduates to suit the vacancies available in institutions.
en_661798_9	Steps had to be taken for the immediate enrolment of students who had passed the Advanced Level Examination last year.
en_661798_10	The discussion focused attention on establishing diploma courses within the university system to produce the workforce needed by the country in the short term.
en_661798_11	Action should be taken to establish Teacher Science Colleges and Hotel Schools targeting the job market.
en_661798_12	He pointed out the importance of using the Batticaloa University as a national resource to be integrated into the national university system.
en_661798_13	He mentioned that the time has come to formulate courses considering the needs of the country.
en_661798_14	Many other topics were also discussed.
en_661798_15	Ministers Bandula Gunawardena, Dulles Alahapperuma and State Minister Ranjith Siyambalapitiya were among those present.
